{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"metadata": {"doc_id": "77b2001cfd06d48334658f172eb13161", "source": "NexaCorp Policy Handbook v5.2", "part": "3. Human Resources Policies", "section": "3.4 Benefits & Employee Wellness", "subsection": "3.4.4 Mental Health & Wellbeing", "raw_content": "NexaCorp recognises that mental health is inseparable from professional performance and personal fulfilment. The following resources are available to all employees and their immediate household members at no cost: Employee Assistance Programme (EAP) via ComPsych\u00ae GuidanceResources: up to 8 free counselling sessions per issue per year; 24/7 crisis line; financial and legal consultation; childcare and eldercare referrals. NexaMind\u2122 App: Curated digital mental wellness platform with guided meditation, sleep content, stress assessments, and therapist video sessions ($0 copay for NexaCorp-enrolled employees). Mental Health Days: 3 designated Mental Health Days per calendar year (in addition to PTO) that may be taken without medical documentation. Announced to manager same-day. Compassionate Leave: Up to 5 paid days per event for bereavement or family crisis, in addition to state-mandated bereavement entitlements. Quarterly Wellbeing Stipend: $150/quarter reimbursable towards gym memberships, fitness equipment, nutrition coaching, or approved wellness expenditures.", "type": "text"}, "page_content": "Part: 3. Human Resources Policies\n            Section: 3.4 Benefits & Employee Wellness\n            Subsection: 3.4.4 Mental Health & Wellbeing", "type": "Document"}}